   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON THIRTY-TWO THE BRONZE SERPENT,</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE ONE HANGING ON A TREE,</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>THE HIND OF THE DAWN, AND</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>THE BRIDEGROOM AND THE BRIDE OUTLINE The bronze serpent: The need for the bronze serpent.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The form of the bronze serpent.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The bronze serpent being lifted up on a pole.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The bronze serpent typifying Christ: Being made sin on our behalf.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Having only the likeness of the flesh of sin but not the poisonous element of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Condemning sin through His crucifixion in the flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The one hanging on a tree: Being one who sinned.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Being one who was cursed.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Typifying Christ: Hanging on the tree for us who sin and deserve death.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Suffering the curse of death for us sinners who deserve death.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>That we might receive the Spirit promised by God.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The hind of the dawn: Typifying the resurrected Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Fresh and active.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>A young hart: Having fellowship with us.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Coming back to meet with us.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The bridegroom and the bride: Typifying Christ and the church.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In His resurrection: Christ being lovely as the Bridegroom.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Obtaining the church as the bride.</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
